id: pm-usfg
title: "SDK-first architecture: pm CLI (and MCP) become thin layers over a complete public pm SDK"
description: "Promote every PM primitive the CLI uses (item lifecycle, queries, annotations, governance, schema/config/profile, history) from src/core internals into the public pm SDK, then rebuild CLI command handlers as thin presentation shims over that SDK so any integrator can build a fully custom PM tool from the SDK alone. Duplicate check: searched SDK-first/boundary/public-primitives items — existing SDK work (pm-ugqx lineage) covers extension authoring only; no open overlap on core-primitive promotion."
type: Epic
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: architecture,"area:cli","area:mcp","area:sdk",refactor
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:51:44.440Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-05T09:05:53.896Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 3600
acceptance_criteria: "Public SDK exposes item lifecycle, query/read, annotation/link, governance/validation, schema/config/profile, and history primitives with typed results; src/cli.ts, src/cli/**, src/mcp.ts, and src/mcp/** cannot grow private src/core imports beyond the SDK boundary ratchet baseline enforced in CI and must shrink toward SDK-only imports as primitives are promoted; an exemplar consumer builds a minimal custom PM CLI using only @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; SDK reference docs cover every promoted primitive; zero CLI behavior change (full test suite green)"
goal: project management = context management
objective: The pm SDK delivers the complete baseline + primitives of a universal PM tool; the CLI is 100% built on it
value: "Universal customization: any project can assemble its own PM tool from SDK primitives; CLI/MCP/SDK can never drift because they share one implementation"
why_now: "Today the SDK covers extension/package authoring (compose/define/runtime/testing) but core primitives (item store, search, history, governance) are src/core internals reachable only through the CLI; the simplification epic (pm-n7rr) needs a stable primitive layer to shim against"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: medium
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T05:51:11.797Z",claude-code-agent,"Progress evidence from child items pm-lodl/pm-8778: SDK-first baseline is now explicit and enforceable. Current private boundary debt is quantified at 857 unique src/core import edges across 91 boundary files (101 scanned) from src/cli.ts, src/cli/**, and src/mcp/**. The static quality gate now prevents growth and stale baseline entries, giving each SDK primitive-promotion lane a measurable ratchet target while preserving the project philosophy 'project management = context management'."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T04:55:45.848Z",maintainer-agent,"Gap analysis 2026-07-05 — src/sdk currently exports extension/package-authoring surfaces only (compose, define, runtime, testing, cli-contracts, profile presets/plan). The PM primitives themselves live in src/core (item, store, search, history, governance, schema, config, session, checkpoint, lock) and src/cli/commands imports them directly; ~60 command modules under src/cli/commands also embed business logic beyond parsing/rendering. Consequence; an SDK-only consumer today cannot create, query, or govern items without shelling out to the CLI."
  "2026-07-05T04:55:46.394Z",maintainer-agent,"Promotion strategy — domain-by-domain (lifecycle, query, annotations, governance, schema/config/profile) with a zero-behavior-change bar per domain; boundary gate (pm-8778) starts as an allowlist ratchet at current import state so it can merge before promotions finish and tighten with each one. Exemplar package (pm-cbwg) is the acceptance proof for the universality story pm-w89s."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T04:55:46.836Z",maintainer-agent,"The CLI-simplification epic pm-n7rr and this epic reinforce each other; consolidated commands should be implemented as thin SDK calls, so the inventory task pm-lodl deliberately feeds both epics and should run before either implementation stream starts."
body: "## Charter\nMake the SDK the single public API of pm. Ordering: (1) inventory the CLI-to-core call graph, (2) promote primitives domain-by-domain into src/sdk with stable typed signatures, (3) flip CLI handlers to consume the SDK, (4) enforce the boundary with a lint/CI gate so it can never regress, (5) prove universality with an SDK-only exemplar consumer.\n\n## Layering target\n- src/core: private implementation detail (no stability promise)\n- src/sdk: the ONLY public programmatic surface — re-exports/wraps core with typed, documented, semver-meaningful contracts\n- src/cli + src/mcp: presentation layers that import exclusively from src/sdk\n- packages/*: already consume the SDK; gain access to the same primitives the CLI uses\n\n## Non-goals\n- No behavior changes to any command (pure re-layering)\n- No new storage formats\n- Extension/package authoring SDK (compose/define/runtime/testing) stays as-is; this epic adds the missing primitive layer beside it\n\n## Relationship to CLI simplification epic pm-n7rr\npm-n7rr consolidates the command surface; this epic supplies the primitives those consolidated commands call. Inventory (child task) feeds both.\n\n## Promotion index update (audit 2026-07-05, second pass)\nGap-check against the full 60+ command surface found three families uncovered by the original five promotion items; filed: pm-4a7m (history-stream maintenance: redact/repair/compact), pm-je50 (plan workflow primitives), pm-oslr (execution & diagnostics: test running + test-run lifecycle, search eval harness, telemetry stats/export). With these, every CLI command family maps to exactly one SDK promotion item; the pm-lodl inventory validates the partition."
